13 french horn, brass arrangement\n* Perry White \u2013 bass clarinet, flute\n* Scott White \u2013 cello, violin\n* Matty Arouse \u2013 fiddle\n* Markus Dirk \u2013 bass trumpet\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|76|id=28275|artist=Mouse On Mars|album=Niun Niggung|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 18, 2018}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Discogs master|15104|Niun Niggung}}\n* {{MusicBrainz release group|mbid=96b033e7-c172-3bbc-ae3e-15ff1b35a96e|name=Niun Niggung}}\n\n[[Category:1999 albums]]\n[[Category:Mouse on Mars albums]]\n[[Category:Rough Trade Records albums]]\n[[Category:Thrill Jockey albums]]\n[[Category:Domino Recording Company albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Niun Niggung\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Mouse on Mars]]\n| cover      = Niun.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|1999}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Dub techno]]|[[intelligent dance music|IDM]]|[[Wonky (genre)|wonky]]|[[glitch music|glitch]]|[[nu jazz]]|[[experimental hip hop]]}}\n| length     = {{Duration|m=62|s=04}}\n| label      = [[Rough Trade Records]], [[Thrill Jockey]], [[Domino Recording Company]], [[Sonig]]\n| producer   = [[Jan St. Werner]], [[Andi Toma]]\n| prev_title = [[Glam (album)|Glam]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[Idiology]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Alternative cover\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = Niun2.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = Thrill Jockey edition\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/niun-niggung-mw0000050644|title=Mouse on Mars - Niun Niggung|work=[[AllMusic]]|first=John|last=Bush|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev2score = favorable<ref name=exclaim>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/mouse_on_mars-niun_niggung|title=Mouse On Mars: Niun Niggung|work=[[Exclaim!]]|first=Andrew|last=Duke|date=February 1, 2000|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev3score = 7.9/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/5459-niun-niggung/|title=Mouse on Mars: Niun Niggung|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|first=Mark|last=Richard-San|date=February 29, 2000|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev4score = favorable<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/mouseonmars-niun/|title=Mouse on Mars: Niun Niggung|work=[[PopMatters]]|first=George|last=Zahora|date=|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Niun Niggung''''' is a studio album by German electronica duo [[Mouse on Mars]]. It was released in 1999. It peaked at number 76 on the [[German Albums Chart]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Mouse on Mars |url=http://www.musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/artist/MOUSE+ON+MARS/longplay |publisher=musicline.de |accessdate=June 17, 2018 |language=de}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nAndrew Duke of ''[[Exclaim!]]'' gave the album a favorable review, describing it as \"an album that immediately becomes a must-have for the electronic music enthusiast.\"<ref name=exclaim/>\n\n''[[The Wire (magazine)|The Wire]]'' named ''Niun Niggung'' the record of the year in its annual critics' poll.<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=99 Rewind: 50 Records of the Year |date=January 2000 |magazine=[[The Wire (magazine)|The Wire]] |issue=190/191 |page=67 |location=London |url=https://reader.exacteditions.com/issues/35087/spread/66 |url-access=subscription |via=[[Exact Editions]]}}</ref> ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' placed it at number 16 on the \"20 Best Albums of 2000\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/2000/12/20-best-albums-2000/mouse-on-mars-niun-niggung/|title=Mouse on Mars, Niun Niggung (Thrill Jockey)|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=November 6, 2014|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'' named it the 33rd best album of 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/bestalbumsandtracksoftheyear/1999-2-1045360|title=Albums And Tracks Of The Year: 1999|work=[[NME]]|date=October 10, 2016|accessdate=January 2, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320225421/http://www.nme.com/bestalbumsandtracksoftheyear/1999-2-1045360|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Rough Trade Records edition\n| title1 = Download Sofist\n| length1 = 2:28\n| title2 = Yippie\n| length2 = 3:51\n| title3 = Pinwheel Herman\n| length3 = 4:46\n| title4 = Super Sonig Fadeout\n| length4 = 4:37\n| title5 = Booosc\n| length5 = 3:15\n| title6 = Diskdusk\n| length6 = 3:50\n| title7 = Gogonal\n| length7 = 5:09\n| title8 = Albion Rose\n| length8 = 3:32\n| title9 = Mompou\n| length9 = 1:55\n| title10 = Distroia\n| length10 = 5:16\n| title11 = Wald F.X.\n| length11 = 4:46\n| title12 = Circloid Bricklett Spr\u00fcngli\n| length12 = 2:18\n| title13 = <!-- Untitled -->\n| length13 = 14:37\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Thrill Jockey edition\n| title1 = Download Sofist\n| length1 = 2:28\n| title2 = Yippie\n| length2 = 3:51\n| title3 = Mykologics\n| length3 = 3:38\n| title4 = Gogonal\n| length4 = 5:09\n| title5 = Diskdusk\n| length5 = 3:50\n| title6 = Pinwheel Herman\n| length6 = 4:46\n| title7 = Dispothek\n| length7 = 5:22\n| title8 = Albion Rose\n| length8 = 3:32\n| title9 = Tensual\n| length9 = 3:35\n| title10 = Distroia\n| length10 = 5:16\n| title11 = Booosc\n| length11 = 3:15\n| title12 = Mompou\n| length12 = 1:55\n| title13 = Wald F.X.\n| length13 = 4:46\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Sonig edition\n| title1 = Download Sofist\n| length1 = 2:28\n| title2 = Yippie\n| length2 = 5:28\n| title3 = Pinwheel Herman\n| length3 = 4:46\n| title4 = Super Sonig Fadeout\n| length4 = 4:37\n| title5 = Booosc\n| leng